              <table id="EditorialReviewsPanel" class="ReviewSection" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Book Description:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1">THE HARVARD BUSINESS REVIEW PAPERBACK SERIES is designed to bring today's managers and professionals the fundamental information they need to stay competitive in a fast-moving world.  Here are the landmark ideas that have established the Harvard Business Review as required reading for ambitious business people in organizations around the globe.    <P>Information Technology (IT) influences all aspects of business today, and this wide-ranging resource will help managers understand the key concepts and terms, and to envision the strategic potential of their IT assets.  The articles provide a candid dialogue on the issues surrounding outsourcing, and take a look at planning for connectivity and control in the year 2000 and beyond.</span>
              
</td></tr></table>
              <table id="CustomerReviewsPanel" class="ReviewSection" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
